5000|$|Floppies are unpartitioned devices {{without a}} RDB and {{also do not}} use the autobooting mechanism, so were only <b>bootable</b> if the disk's dostype was one the ROM-based {{filesystem}} understood. As a result, FFS-formatted floppies were not <b>bootable</b> until the release of Kickstart 2.0, and mounting them under Workbench 1.3 involved some ugly unsupported hacks. Similarly, [...] "Directory Cache" [...] variants were not <b>bootable</b> or supported until Kickstart 3.0.|$|E
