5000|$|Rufus {{supports}} {{a variety of}} <b>bootable</b> [...]iso files, including various Linux distributions and Windows installation [...]iso files, as well as raw disk image files (including compressed ones). If needed, it will install a bootloader such as SYSLINUX or GRUB onto the flash drive to render it <b>bootable.</b> It also allows the installation of MS-DOS or FreeDOS onto a flash drive {{as well as the}} creation of Windows To Go <b>bootable</b> media. It supports formatting flash drives as FAT, FAT32, NTFS, exFAT, UDF or ReFS filesystems.|$|E
